<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-1861">
<p>That&#8217;s interesting that you mentioned the UK. It doesn&#8217;t quite surprise me that the law requires you to disclose encryption keys. I have traveled to many countries (including countries with poor human rights record such as Syria and Egypt) and I have to say that the UK border control is BY FAR the most abusive I&#8217;ve come across. I&#8217;ve been to that country 4 times and every time I&#8217;ve come, the border officers have drilled me with ridiculous questions. I am a law abiding US citizens with no criminal record. However, I am not Caucasian. Upon the latest entry, the officer reviewed every stamp in my passport, asked about my job, asked to see a copy of my bank statement (didn&#8217;t have that with me, but who does?), asked to look at my credit card to see the expiration date, asked for my driver&#8217;s license, and lastly wanted to make a copy of my ATM card. I am not making this up. After an hour of interrogation, the officer let me enter.</p>
</div>
